	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't know much about video cards, but I think an i5 and just 4GB of RAM is a bit low for a gaming PC by today's standards. My laptop has that configuration, but I bought exactly 1 year ago, and even back then this was a modest setup. I believe that the video card is the most crucial thing for gaming, but PCs get outdated really fast, so you really don't wanna go cheap on the rest.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
