	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I can't say it would affect gaming performance directly (it helps when loading interrupts gameplay), but I wouldn't go without a solid-state drive for the OS and main games/apps, then a larger traditional drive for everything else.  In my experience, games like Team Fortress 2 that previously took a minute to load now take more like 5 seconds, after moving an SSD.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


