		<td><b>Re: Help with computer build.</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Major-label PC games tend not to require much more CPU than is present in the consoles that are popular when it is released. A 3 GHz quad core already beats the Xbox 360 (three in-order Power cores with 2-way SMT instead of out-of-order, clocked at 3.2 GHz) and the Wii U (three PowerPC G3 cores clocked at 1.25 GHz). Indie games, with their lower art budgets, tend to require even less CPU (except, I'm told, certain simulations like Dwarf Fortress).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


